column1: #Text=An old analog television , scheduled to stop working after the Feb. 17 digital transition .

#Text=One month from the February 17 scheduled transition from analog to digital television broadcast in the United States , members of the United States Senate have introduced a bill that would push back the transition four months later , to June 12 .

#Text=This is due to concerns raised about the government 's subsidy program for digital TV receiver boxes , which has run out of money with over 1 million televisions in the United States still running on analog .
#Text=" In Minnesota , more than 21 % of our households depend exclusively on over-the-air broadcast TV .
